cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.CY

This paper discusses the application of data mining techniques in web data, specifically in web usage mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the organization and retrieval of information from the web. The paper also discusses various data mining techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper discusses the preprocessing of web log data, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
